{{NRIS-only|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox NRHP | name = Lebanon National Cemetery | nrhp_type = | image = | caption = | nearest_city= [[Lebanon, Kentucky]] | lat_degrees = 37 | lat_minutes = 33 | lat_seconds = 09 | lat_direction = N | long_degrees = 85 | long_minutes = 16 | long_seconds = 07 | long_direction = W | coord_display = inline,title | locmapin = Kentucky#USA | built = 1863 | architecture = | added = June 05, 1975 | area = {{convert|2.8|acre}} | governing_body = [[U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs]] | refnum = 75000801<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref> }} '''Lebanon National Cemetery''' is a [[United States National Cemetery]] located just outside the city of [[Lebanon, Kentucky|Lebanon]] in [[Marion County, Kentucky]]. Administered by the [[United States Department of Veterans Affairs]], it encompasses {{convert|14.8|acre}} and as of the end of 2005 it had 4,699 interments. It is administered by the [[Zachary Taylor National Cemetery]].
==History== First established in 1862 as a cemetery for nearby Camp Crittenden, the [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]] supply depot in Lebanon, and the military hospitals in the area. It was designated a National Cemetery in 1867. Two donations of land in the 1980s expanded the cemetery to its current size.
Lebanon National Cemetery was placed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1975.
